=Description=
  	
'''Democratizing Access to Legal Information...'''

Around the world, legal information is generally available in proportion to a person’s economic resources, which means that often those who need it the most have the least access to it.

Our belief is that rights that one has to pay to learn about are not rights, but privileges.

Law Underground's objective is to provide free access to legal information.


'''...Through Collaborative Web Resources'''

Law Underground produces dynamically-generated interviews. At the end of each interview, personalized descriptions about your legal rights and practical options are presented, free of extraneous and confusing information.

Legal content is amassed through an online collaboration by lawyers and law students.

Law Underground, Inc. is a non-profit organization located in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania.


